		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Where are the N-64 clone consoles?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have seen many clone consoles of the NES, Genesis and SNES as well as the new Atari 2600 clone that was just put out, but I haven't really seen any clone N-64's. <br /><br />I'm not super up to date on the patents expiring or anything, but I was guessing that all of the protection Nintendo had on the NES has expired and thus that is why there are so many clone consoles out there plus it may have not been that hard of a task. The closest I've seen to a N-64 clone is someone putting a raspberry pie in a shell with a N-64 emulator in it. <br /><br />So when do you think we will see some N-64 clone consoles? Any guesses?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


